<MethodEndpoint
  method={"delete"}
  path={"/api/v1.0/parts/{PartId}"}
  context={"endpoint"}
>
  
</MethodEndpoint>



Deletes a part by its unique identifier. Use this when a part is retired or should no longer be offered in ticket or inventory workflows.

**Prerequisites**
1. **PartId** - Use [GET /api/v1.0/parts](/docs/api/parts/list-parts) or [POST /api/v1.0/parts/search](/docs/api/parts/search-parts) and extract `Items[].PartId`.

**Workflow Example**
1. Identify the PartId to remove.
2. [DELETE /api/v1.0/parts/\{PartId\}](/docs/api/parts/delete-part).
3. Confirm removal by re-running [GET /api/v1.0/parts](/docs/api/parts/list-parts).

**Minimal Required Fields**: PartId (path).
